.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH describe 1  "describe " 
.SH NAME
describe \- Add or update a key description
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmurk describe\fR [\fB\-\-example\fR] [\fB\-\-tag\fR] [\fB\-\-rotate\-every\fR] [\fB\-\-expires\fR] [\fB\-\-vault\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIKEY\fR> <\fIDESCRIPTION\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Add or update a key description
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-example\fR \fI<EXAMPLE>\fR
Example value
.TP
\fB\-\-tag\fR \fI<TAG>\fR
Tag for grouping (repeatable, replaces existing tags)
.TP
\fB\-\-rotate\-every\fR \fI<DAYS>\fR
Rotation interval, e.g. `90d` or `90` (days); `never` clears it
.TP
\fB\-\-expires\fR \fI<DATE>\fR
Hard expiry date, e.g. `2026\-09\-01`; `never` clears it
.TP
\fB\-\-vault\fR \fI<VAULT>\fR [default: .murk]
Vault filename
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIKEY\fR>
Secret key name
.TP
<\fIDESCRIPTION\fR>
Description text
